The paper proposes a method for fake fingerprint detection using a convolutional neural network, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The problem being addressed is related to biometric security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of a neural network for classification suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of memory, which could indicate a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves image processing and feature extraction, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
